<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-107-264  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 107 264.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Nov 20 1989 v3 n47 p32(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD ADP cuts reduced under Gramm-Rudman.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob; Taylor, Kymberly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A draft copy of the 1990 Defense appropriations bill reveals thatDepartment of Defense (DOD) data processing operations andmaintenance budgets will be reduced by more than the 4.3 percentdecrease imposed by the Gramm-Rudman-Hollings law.andP;  The bill alsorequires consolidation of all automated Army accounting systemsinto a single, integrated, management plan and calls forformulation of a plan to resolve Army and Navy data processingproblems uncovered by recent audits.andP;  The bill provides increasedfunding for research on neural networks, integrated command andcontrol systems, high-definition TV, and X-ray lithography.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     LegislationEDP BudgetingGovernment AgencyReductionData ProcessingAutomationUnited States. Department of Defense.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   DOD ADP budgets and cuts. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>